        <ul style="list-style-type:disc">
            <li>
                In Hajj Qiran, ‘Umrah and Hajj are performed with a single Ihram
            </li>
            <li>
                One who performs Qiran hajj is called Qaarin
            </li>
            <li>
                In Qiran Hajj, Qaarin enters into Ihram with an intention to perform ‘umrah and hajj together, without any break in between
            </li>
            <li>
                Majority scholars rule that for this type of Hajj,  it is a prerequisite for the pilgrim (Qaarin) to have the sacrificial animal with them
            </li>
        </ul>

